    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-30T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–3050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-30T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 30, 1950—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 150. Reur 345 and treatment of Indians
                    in South Africa. Dept has given careful consideration Del views on US voting
                    position on res in Plenary. Dept believes US vote in plenary shld be as follows
                    on questionable parts of res: <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Vote in favor second operative para;</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Abstain on last para preamble;</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Support vote in segments on third operative para. Vote against last
                            clause. If last clause not eliminated abstain on para as a whole.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Vote in favor of res as a whole whether or not last para preamble and
                            last clause operative para three are eliminated.<note n="1"
                                xml:id="d324fn1">In the voting on the resolution by the General
                                Assembly in plenary meeting on December 2, the United States
                                Delegation voted as instructed herein except that no plenary vote
                                was held on the third operative paragraph as a whole. For the
                                proceedings of the General Assembly on this matter, see United
                                Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Records of the General Assembly,
                                    Fifth Session, Plenary Meetings</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                    >i</hi>, pp. 529 ff. For the text of the resolution as adopted
                                (Resolution 395 (V)), see United Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                                    Records of the General Assembly, Fifth Session, Resolutions, 19
                                    September to 15 December 1950</hi>, p. 24.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
